    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-12T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-12T07:00:00-05:00" n="617"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d617">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002 Manchuria/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain (<persName corresp="#p_AR1"
                            type="from">Atherton</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-12T12:00:00+00:00"
                            >March 12, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received March 12—9:20
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>107. Foreign Office informed me this morning it had received information
                    corresponding with paragraph 1 of Department’s 88, March 11, 1 p.m. Foreign
                    Office intimated its realization that some action along the lines of the
                    Department’s suggestion must be taken but could give no considered opinion
                    before consultation with <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1">Sir John Simon</persName>
                    who returns from the Continent tomorrow evening.</p>
                <p>I understand Minister <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">Wilson</persName> was unable to
                    communicate the contents of Department’s 88, March 11, 1 p.m., to <persName
                        corresp="#p_SSJ1">Simon</persName> before he left Geneva for Paris last
                    evening.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
